summaries.short: Dory escapes, Drew’s past resurfaces, Portia meets her movie’s director, and Elliott embraces his new role at the network.
summaries.full: Dory escapes while Chip is distracted by his busybody neighbor Paula Jo, who believes he’s a woman named Lylah. Drew’s old life threatens to disrupt his newfound happiness. Portia meets the imperious director of her movie. Elliott steps into his new role at the network.

summaries.short: Chip drags Dory back to the house, where a nosy Paula Jo awaits. Drew rushes back to New York after seeing something strange on social, Portia has a bleak first day on set, and Elliott gains even more notoriety.
summaries.full: Chip drags an exhausted and defeated Dory back to the house, where a nosy Paula Jo awaits. Drew rushes back to New York after seeing something troubling on social media. At their new jobs, Portia has a less than stellar first day on set, and Elliott gains even more notoriety.

summaries.short: Dory tries to break out of her felt prison, Drew starts a new life at a theme park, Portia auditions for the film adaption of the trial, and Elliott reconsiders his political beliefs for a chance to host his own talk show.
summaries.full: Dory tries to escape from her felt prison and the obsessed fan we now know as Chip. Meanwhile, Drew starts a new life at a theme park as “Prince Grisly,” Portia auditions to be “Portia” in the film adaptation of the trial, and Elliott reconsiders his political beliefs for a chance to host his own news talk show.
